paladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=dyermaker>Dyermaker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Knight Of the Realm</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/22/02 11:07:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14996.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dueling advice</span><hr size=1> The duel begins before the combatants agree to it. You need to combat your opponent in the head game before the duel begins. Start off with comments like &quot;I am trying to play an honorable Paladin, it would be wrong of me to embarass you like that&quot; and &quot;should I limit myself to my first circle of spells, you know, to keep you in the battle more than 2 seconds?&quot;. Mess with their head. In my experience, the longer you keep them wanting it, the easier it is to crush them. :)<br><br>When duelling either a cleric or a druid, keep your resists up. Cleric will have almost no offense and the druid will be all spell offense. Keep your Cancel Magic memmed against these two. They will get frustrated and waste their mana re-buffing instead of blasting. Let them waste their mana defensively you have the advantage. If they get off a debuff on you, having Cancel Magic handy will be great too.<br><br>Keep alternate equipment handy if you need to change tactics. Once the Druid gives up casting against you and decides to charm something to battle you, if you have a swap for AC gear you take away that advantage too! This works best if you've played the head games, they stop thinking about what you're doing and about what they should be doing, and you'll keep control of the combat.<br><br>I usually play in first person mode... I am an old time Doom II/Duke 3d player, and that's what's most comfortable to me for regular game sessions. Change this view in a duel to see the largest area possible! If you see them behind you, then they can't run away as easily. They WILL try and run away.<br><br>Taunt them during combat. Remember, these people *DARED* challenge you. Make them regret the beating they are taking. Make sure they know that you are the better person. <br><br>Do not taunt after you win. Paladins don't taunt over a fallen opponent. It makes them think you weren't all that confident in the first place. <p>Dyermaker Merdinho -- The Lost Paladin and Lil'Bastard<BR>42 Paladin of Tunare, Quellious Server<BR>Profiles: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Magelo<A> -- <A HREF="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/userinfo.html?char=16712">Allakhazam</A> --<A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=3366">Caster's Realm</A><BR>Lil'Bastard Clan: <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32626">Dyermaker</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91012">Chapado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=115022">Chiad</A>  | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=82578">Malvado</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=92554">Narnya</A> | <A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=111438">Solyony</A> <BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=14996.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=14996.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14996.topic&index=3><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID